defaultThe Government policy focus should be to ensure this level of growth is minimised and funding is provided to metropolitan areas to develop integrated public transport networ
defaultk to support this growth. Such investment would ensure the ‘double win’ of preventing the economic and environmental impacts of the otherwise predicted traffic growth as well in itself supporting economic growth and reducing environmental impacts to the be
defaultnefit of residents and businesses located in our core cities and within their economic geographies.
default2
default5
default.
default              
defaultOverall, these strategic and local levels of traffic growth would be extremely detrimental to the economic and environment objectives of both the West M
defaultidlands and the wider UK. It is crucial the Government ensures a focus on providing the policy framework to ensure the majority of these trips occur in a sustainable manner with a focus on rail for interurban trips and public transport, walking and cycling
default for local trips. This is likely to involve a balanced approach to supply and demand.
