default4
default1
default.
default              
defaultIn order to support and facilitate 
defaultlocal economic growth, the Highways Agency 
defaultneeds to be a proactive partner who works with local authorities, developers and others to deliver a strategic road network which can support economic growth. This approach would complement the guidance provided w
defaultithin the recently published Department for Transport Circular 02/2013 ‘The Strategic Road Network and the Delivery of Sustainable Development’. At present the Highways Agency is very reactive, especially in regards to development and impact upon the SRN. 
defaultWhilst this is understandable for motorway routes, other non-motorway routes could be planned and managed more flexibly to support connectivity to potential development sites.
